Renèe Estella is a model and social media personality with more than 800K followers on Instagram.

1000-step TI trained on a dataset of 18 images with my usual settings.

Appreciate my work? My TIs are free, but you can always buy me a coffee. :)

Curious about my work process? I have summarized it here.

How to create a good prompt using my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there. For instance, "photo of (r3nestella:0.99), a woman, RAW, close portrait photo, bodysuit with zipper, cleavage, fishnet stockings, pale skin, slim body, (high detailed skin:1.2), 8k uhd, dslr, soft lighting, high quality, film grain, Fujifilm XT3 sharp focus, f 5.6".

Gothic Horror Style

файл на civitaiстраница на civitai

Yet Another horror style on Civitai :)

About

A style for generating dark (visually an thematically) Gothic Horror style pictures. This was put together using the Embedding Inspector addon. I combined visually and thematically dark vectors into an embedding with weightings I liked. This style doesn't do anything special, other than guide your checkpoint to a horror themed result.

If you're an experienced prompt crafter, you probably don't need this, and could generate similar results with out it.

Installation

Place in the directory where you keep your embeddings

Usage

Use style-gothic-horror in your prompt. Placement location in the prompt really matters with this one. Placement at the beginning of the prompt creates visually dark images, (this works with noise offset lora, or models that include noise offset). Placement at the end of the prompt will give you more visual flexibility. Experiment with placing it at the beginning, middle or end of your prompt.

Easy Photorealism v1.0

файл на civitaiстраница на civitai

This is a Textual Inversion i've made for fast photo-realism.

It comes with positive and negative TI. Use it with weight do difference.

Download all 2 files from "files option" in top right.

Put in embeddings folder and use it like any other embed.

Usage:

Prompt: your prompt, kkw-ph1

Negative prompt: kkw-ph1-neg

Don't know why civitai striped out from data.

You also can use the negative as standard for all other type of work.

Use it in img2img to port 3d render and other work to real

just put

Prompt: subject, kkw-ph1

Negative prompt: kkw-ph1-neg

Set cfg to 30 and denoise lower( 0.18) for test, then move it for get better result.

This setting is for image like Daz3d image, if you use anime or really flat image, you have to go up with denoise value.

Also remember more high is denoise, more lower you need cfg to keep image consistance.

An embedding of actress Hilarie Burton, mostly trained on images of her One Three Hill days. It can also serve as an embedding for the character of Peyton Sawyer, otherwise known as many teen boys' wet dream in the early 2000's.

512x512 or 512x768
